SymEngine need some Prerequisites tools and external libraries to build...

Prerequisites
1-Install CMake: Download and install CMake from cmake.org. Ensure CMake is added to your system PATH.
2-Install Visual Studio: Make sure you have Visual Studio installed with the "Desktop development with C++" workload.
3-Install Git: Download and install Git from git-scm.com.

Install External Libraries
1-Install vcpkg and install gmp mpfr mpc flint llvm through vcpkg, if you have enough RAM, and a powerful CPU

git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg.git (Clone the vcpkg repository)
cd vcpkg
.\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat

.\vcpkg install gmp mpfr mpc flint llvm (Install required libraries using vcpkg)

2- if not... you need to download and install the required libraries: GMP, MPFR, MPC, FLINT, and LLVM, ensuring compatibility with Windows step by step, to do so..
 1. GMP (https://gmplib.org/)
    Download the Windows build (zip or tar.xz).
    Extract the downloaded file.
    Open a Visual Studio Developer Command Prompt or MinGW64
    Navigate to the extracted directory.

    cd gmp-<version>
    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/gmp
    make
    make install

 2. MPFR (https://www.mpfr.org/mpfr-4.2.1/)
    Download the latest tar.xz file.
    Extract the downloaded file.
    Open a Visual Studio Developer Command Prompt or MinGW64
    Navigate to the extracted directory.

    cd mpfr-<version>
    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/mpfr --with-gmp=/usr/local/gmp
    make
    make install

 3. MPC (https://directory.fsf.org/wiki/Mpc)
    Download the latest tar.gz file.
    Extract the downloaded file.
    Open a Visual Studio Developer Command Prompt or MinGW64
    Navigate to the extracted directory.

    cd mpc-<version>
    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/mpc --with-gmp=/usr/local/gmp --with-mpfr=/usr/local/mpfr
    make
    make install

 4. FLINT (https://github.com/flintlib/flint/releases/tag/v3.1.3-p1)
    Navigate to the "Releases" section of the repository and download the latest stable release tarball
    Extract the tarball:
    tar -xzf flint-latestversion.tar.gz
    cd flint-latestversion

    Configure FLINT to use the static GMP library:
    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/flint --with-gmp=/usr/local/gmp --enable-static --disable-shared

    Build and install FLINT:
    make
    make install

 5. LLVM (https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/releases/tag/llvmorg-18.1.6)
    For building and integrating SymEngine with Visual Studio on a 64-bit Windows system, you should download the 64-bit pre-built binaries of LLVM
    
    Run the installer:
    Double-click the downloaded .exe file to run the installer.
    During installation, ensure that the option to add LLVM to the system PATH is selected. This allows the clang and clang++ compilers to be easily accessible from any command prompt or terminal.

    Verify the installation:
    clang --version

Building SymEngine
1. Clone the SymEngine repository: 
git clone https://github.com/symengine/symengine.git
cd symengine

2. Create a build directory:
mkdir build
cd build

3.Configure SymEngine to use the static libraries:
cmake -G "MSYS Makefiles" -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="/usr/local/gmp;/usr/local/mpfr;/usr/local/mpc;/usr/local/flint;/path/to/llvm" -DWITH_GMP=ON -DWITH_MPFR=ON -DWITH_MPC=ON -DWITH_FLINT=ON -DWITH_LLVM=ON .. 
(cmake -G "MSYS Makefiles" -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="C:\Users\akermansaravi\Desktop\gitRepo\gmp-6.3.0\gmp-6.3.0;C:\Users\akermansaravi\Desktop\gitRepo\mpfr-4.2.1\mpfr-4.2.1;C:\Users\akermansaravi\Desktop\gitRepo\mpc-1.3.1\mpc-1.3.1;C:\Users\akermansaravi\Desktop\gitRepo\flint-3.1.3-p1\flint-3.1.3-p1;C:\Program Files\LLVM" -DWITH_GMP=ON -DWITH_MPFR=ON -DWITH_MPC=ON -DWITH_FLINT=ON -DWITH_LLVM=ON ..
)

4. Build and Install SymEngine: 
make
make install





